				<p><strong><em>The Grand Doctor Upledger</em></strong><br />
					Another fortuitous meeting was with Doctor John E. Upledger who was a pioneer in the psycho-emotional connection and movement of the cranial bones. &quot;These certainly are the best hands I have ever seen,&quot; Jean-Pierre Barral repeatedly said about John E. Upledger. John E. Upledger and Jean-Pierre Barral liked to exchange their ideas on how to enhance the care for their patients, while at the same time, preserving their own original ideas and treatment developments.</p>
				<p><strong><em>The Upledger Institute</em></strong><br />
					As early as 1985, Barral presented Visceral Manipulation courses in the United States organized through the Florida-based Upledger Institute. These courses were highly successful, and that was one of the reasons for the creation of the Barral Institute.  It was through the Upledger Institute that the seminars were developed and the Barral Institute was born.</p>
				<p><strong><em>The Barral Institute</em></strong><br />
					The entire academic and administrative staff of the Barral Institute voted on the name of the newly formed company - the Barral Institute.  The name &quot;Barral Institute&quot; was chosen partly because &quot;Barral&quot; was already known throughout the world.  Only Jean-Pierre Barral voted against using this name as he did not want others to think he was using his name out of ego.</p>
				<p>The Barral Institute is comprised of an American administrative staff directed by the son of John E. Upledger, John Matthew Upledger, and about twenty Teachers from America, Canada, Europe and the United Kingdom. Gail Wetzler is the Director of Curriculum. The Barral Institute teaches seminars in about 30 countries and continues to grow each year.</p>
